HEADWORD: Duces tecum
<hw>Du"ces te"cum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., bring with
thee.]</ety> <def>A judicial process commanding a person to appear in
court and bring with him some piece of evidence or other thing to be
produced to the court.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Duchess</ent>⟦br⟧
